{"title":"Carbon brake calipers and a broken stem: The sub-4.6kg Cannondale SuperSix Evo","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cannondale-supersix-evo-hill-climb-bike","date":1698850949000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cannondale-supersix-evo-hill-climb-bike\">Carbon brake calipers and a broken stem: The sub-4.6kg Cannondale SuperSix Evo</a></p>\n\n<p>Hill climb events are notorious for their weight-weenie builds and none took that further than Paul Roby with his Cannondale SuperSix Evo. The full build came in at a staggering 4.56kg, one of the very few to break the 5kg mark on the day. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Roby’s SuperSix Evo features Ciamillo Lekki 8 carbon brake calipers and Lightweight Gipfelsturm carbon wheels (great for shaving the grams though it would’ve been a slippery ride back down). </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Roby had planned to use a full Darimo cockpit for the race but, as sometimes happens with such marginal builds, tragedy struck and his Darimo stem broke just weeks before the event, forcing him to swap in a Deda alloy alternative. </p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/wiggle-black-friday-clearance-sales\">Wiggle starts Black Friday a month early: Here are the best deals</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-cycling-overshoes\">Best cycling overshoes 2023 reviewed: Waterproof protection for your feet</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">Best road bikes: Best bikes from under £1,000 to over £10,000</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>Considering the change, not to mention the bar tape which is almost unheard of on such light builds, we have to wonder – just how light could this bike be next year? </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-8-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Carbon Ciamillo Lekki 8 brake calipers – the stuff of weight-weenie legend.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-7-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Carbon flanges with carbon spokes make the Lightweight wheels… well… lightweight…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Just in case you weren’t sure.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-4-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A KMC hollow chain, SRAM Red mechanical shifting and featherweight linked cable housing. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-3-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Rotor Aldhu carbon cranks with a 38t chainring.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-6-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>What could have been – a failed Darimo stem saw a last minute Deda replacement to get this bike to the start line.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/11/cannondale_hill_climb_nationals_2023-5-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Charlotte Head</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A Gelu K-4 carbon saddle to finish it off.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Paul Roby’s Cannondale SuperSix Evo spec</h2>\n\n\n\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Frameset</td><td>Cannondale SuperSix Evo</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Weight</td><td>4.56kg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Wheels</td><td>Lightweight Gipfelsturm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Brakes</td><td>Ciamillio Lekki 8 rim brake carbon callipers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Groupset</td><td>SRAM Red mechanical</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Crankset</td><td>Rotor Aldhu, 38t chainring</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Cockpit</td><td>Darimo Ellipse carbon handlebars, Deda alloy stem</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Saddle</td><td>Gelu K-4</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cannondale-supersix-evo-hill-climb-bike\">Carbon brake calipers and a broken stem: The sub-4.6kg Cannondale SuperSix Evo</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"13fec29cb1755faf4603f24ba1f5260abef935ad75906efd690656330c930b90","category":"Cycling"}